'''sacrilicious''' (adjective) - 1. a)so delicious as to be a slight against Christian religious tenants and/or the Christian God. b) a portmanteau of 'sacreligious' and 'delicious' (''The real angel in the Angel Cake made it absolutely sacrilicious!'')  2. sacreligious in a deliciously ironic way 3. a portmanteau of 'sacred' and 'delicious' (''Man, this Body of Christ is sacrilicious!'')